---
/**
 * Privacy notice — v1 placeholder.
 *
 * Per archive/v1/DECISIONS.md D8: no analytics, no third-party trackers. The privacy
 * posture is honest: the site collects nothing client-side. Form submissions
 * via Formspree are covered by Formspree's own privacy practices, linked.
 *
 * Full notice text to be refined with Bell before launch.
 * [PENDING BELL APPROVAL on final privacy notice wording]
 */
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base
  title="Privacy"
  description="3MIP runs no analytics and no third-party trackers. This notice explains what is and isn't collected when you use this site."
>
  <article class="page">
    <h1>Privacy</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      3MIP runs no analytics and no third-party trackers on this site. We do
      not set cookies. We do not log visits beyond what Vercel keeps for
      operational purposes.
    </p>

    <h2>What we collect</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>When you visit a page:</strong> nothing client-side. No analytics
      script, no fingerprinting. Vercel, our static host, retains standard
      access logs (IP, user agent) for security and abuse prevention.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>When you submit the participation form:</strong> the information
      you enter (name, affiliation, email, modeling approach, research question)
      is sent to Formspree, our form processor, and forwarded to project
      coordination at Cornell. We use this information to follow up about
      registration and to send dataset access. We do not share it with third
      parties. Formspree's own
      <a href="https://formspree.io/legal/privacy-policy/" rel="noopener noreferrer">privacy policy</a>
      governs how they handle the submission in transit.
    </p>

    <h2>What we do not do</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>No Google Analytics, Vercel Analytics, Plausible, or any other analytics service.</li>
      <li>No social-media tracking pixels.</li>
      <li>No advertising scripts.</li>
      <li>No cookies set by this site. (Formspree may set a session cookie during form submission.)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>If you have questions or want your data deleted</h2>
    <p>
      Email <a href="mailto:mk2674@cornell.edu">mk2674@cornell.edu</a>.
    </p>

  </article>
</Base>

<style>
  .page {
    max-width: 45rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: var(--space-7) var(--space-3) var(--space-8);
  }
  @media (min-width: 768px) { .page { padding: var(--space-8) var(--space-5); } }
  .lede {
    font-size: var(--text-body-lg);
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
    margin-top: var(--space-3);
    max-width: 60ch;
  }
  .page h2 { margin: var(--space-6) 0 var(--space-3); }
  .page p { margin: 0 0 var(--space-3); max-width: 65ch; }
  .page ul {
    list-style-type: square;
    padding-left: var(--space-4);
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
  }
  .page li { padding-block: var(--space-1); max-width: 60ch; }
  .pending-note {
    margin-top: var(--space-6);
    color: var(--color-ink-subtle);
    font-size: var(--text-small);
  }
</style>
